Privacy Policy for Pay Splitter
Last Updated: June 2026

Welcome to Pay Splitter. We are committed to protecting your personal information and your right to privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and safeguard your data when you use our application.

1. Information We Collect
When you use Pay Splitter, we collect the following information:

Profile Information: Your basic account details, such as your name and email address, provided during authentication.
App Data: Information related to your trips, shared expenses, settlements, and digital pot balances.
2. How We Use Your Data
The data we collect is strictly used to provide the core functionality of the app:

To seamlessly sync your expenses and balances across all your devices.
To share expense details securely with the specific users you invite to your private trips.
To provide secure authentication and access to your account.
We do not sell, rent, or trade your personal data to any third parties.
3. Data Deletion and Your Rights
You have full control over your personal data. You have the right to permanently delete your account and all associated data at any time.

How to delete your data: You can instantly delete your account by opening the app, navigating to the Profile menu, and selecting the "Delete Account" option. This action is permanent and cannot be undone.
4. Third-Party Services
We use Google Firebase to provide secure authentication and real-time database hosting. Your data is stored securely on their servers in strict compliance with industry-standard security protocols and encryption.

5. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact the developer via the support channels provided in the application.
